  "text": "Analysis of proliferation after siRNA-treatment. After demonstrating gene knock-down, we tested whether treatment with siRNA-NRP alters functional properties of tumor cells. Selected colon cancer cell lines were transfected with siRNA-NRP or siRNA-CONT as described above and analyzed for changes in proliferation. Proliferation was examined with tetrazolium (MTT); cells were washed with PBS and incubated with MTT at 37˚C for 45 min. MTT was solubilised with DMSO for 15 min and optical density was determined at 550 nm [CITATION_1] .",
